last_episode_to_air.name: Matty's Icelandic Adventure
last_episode_to_air.overview: Newly crowned Michelin Star Chef (and possible Viking), Ragnar Erikkson, guides Matty through an Icelandic winter wonderland of odd food, crazy buggy rides, and steamy hot springs.

name: Dead Set on Life
overview: From $6 subs to the most sought-after ingredients on the planet—Matty Matheson eats it all, with friends new and old.

episodes.name: The Life of Matty
episodes.overview: Matty takes his mentor Rang Nguyen back to his hometown and down memory lane, showing us where he came from the how he became the chef he is today.

episodes.name: City Matty, Country Matty
episodes.overview: Canadian Chef Matty Matheson checks out Ontario Farms, Perth Pork and Y. U. Ranch and throws an epic BBQ for his friends at his parent's house in Stratford, Ontario.

episodes.name: The Matty of Manila
episodes.overview: Canadian Chef Matty Matheson heads to Winnipeg and hosted by Ron and "Hot Rod" Cantiveros learns how to make Longanisa sausages and cooks at a traditional Filipino Boodle Fight.

episodes.name: Pow Wow Wow
episodes.overview: Invited by the Long Plain First Nation Reserve, Matty travels to Portage La Prairie as a guest of their annual Pow Wow. He participates in a sweat lodge, and learns to Fancy Dance.

episodes.name: Where the Bison Roam
episodes.overview: Matty meets Ivan Smith, the Bison Whisperer in Alberta and learns the ins-and-outs of raising bison. Matty travels to meet up with Chef Edgar Gutierrez for an off-road adventure.

episodes.name: North of Saskatoon
episodes.overview: Matty goes to Saskatchewan for the Great Prairie Feast. Then he heads to a cabin for a wild weekend of duck hunting and blowing shit up.

episodes.name: Super Nova...Scotia
episodes.overview: Matty hits Nova Scotia for lobster fishing and visits chef Bryan Picard’s Bite House. On their way back to Halifax they hit a cheese farm for some award winning Gouda.

episodes.name: The Prodigal Rang Returns
episodes.overview: Rang and Matty pick up where they left off in Episode One but this time in Newfoundland. The dynamic duo’s tour ends up with moose hunting.

episodes.name: Louisiana Mardi Gras
episodes.overview: In the season one finale, Matty goes deep into the heart of Louisiana in search of the original Mardi Gras. After that, Matty meets up with bounce artist Cheeky Blakk in New Orleans to attend the city's largest event of the year.

episodes.name: Rang's Journey
episodes.overview: In the second-season premiere, Matty and Rang visit Rang's hometown in southern Vietnam, where Matty meets his family and learns the story of how he immigrated to Canada.

episodes.name: The French Connection
episodes.overview: Matty and Rang travel to Hanoi to check out the growing restaurant scene. Later, the guys meet with French ex-pats to sample French-inspired Vietnamese food.

episodes.name: Matty, Son of Bear
episodes.overview: French Canadians are known for having a strong cultural identity. Matty investigates the uniqueness of Quebecois culture through a number of unusual subcultures, including LARPing!

episodes.name: Mardi Gras, a Young Man's Game
episodes.overview: Matty travels to New Orleans to witness two different Mardi Gras celebrations, Lundi Gras in the Lower Ninth Ward and Cajun Mardi Gras in Lafayette Square.

episodes.name: Kosher Montreal
episodes.overview: Matty visits one of the oldest Jewish communities in Canada. Then "Hipster Rabbi" takes Matty on a tour of Montreal's kosher-food spots.

episodes.name: The High Cost of Arctic Living
episodes.overview: Matty visits an Inuit community in the Arctic, where he learns about how high food costs are impacting their traditions.

episodes.name: Caribananas
episodes.overview: Matty participates in a Caribana celebration and learns about West Indian culture while visiting Toronto.

episodes.name: If It Ain't Rough, It Ain't Fun
episodes.overview: Matty ventures into the everglades under the protection of Shelley Wooten, an eighth-generation Floridian fighting to keep the hardcore culture of the Gladesmen alive.

episodes.name: The BBQ King of Hollywood
episodes.overview: Matty catches up with chef, Adam Perry Lang as he plans the opening of his new L.A. restaurant. Together, they enjoy some BBQ, boxing, fishing, knife-making and arson.

episodes.name: Vegas, the Prime Rib Capital of America
episodes.overview: Matty and Master Rang head to Vegas in a Caddy convertible to shoot machine guns, try their luck as cowboys, and uncover the secrets of great prime rib.

episodes.name: Born and Raised on the Boardwalk
episodes.overview: Matty hangs with reformed gangsters, Spanto and 2Tone of Born X Raised, who are two Venice Beach natives fighting to save the spirit of their hometown against gentrification.

episodes.name: The Real Australian Outback
episodes.overview: Matty teams up with former soldier turned chef, "Sniper" Steve Austin, for a culinary adventure in the deadly outback of Australia's Northern Territory.

episodes.name: Two Big Chefs in Kiwi Country
episodes.overview: Tā Moko tattoos, mud baths, mussel harvests and a Hāngī cookout. Matty gets the full Māori experience on New Zealand's North Island with master chef, Morgan McGlone.

episodes.name: Thunder Bay, Greatest City in the World
episodes.overview: With its posh ice fishing and frozen lake car races, Chef Hayden Johnston tries to convince Matty that his Thunder Bay home is "The Greatest City in the World."

episodes.name: Matty's Icelandic Adventure
episodes.overview: Newly crowned Michelin Star Chef (and possible Viking), Ragnar Erikkson, guides Matty through an Icelandic winter wonderland of odd food, crazy buggy rides, and steamy hot springs.
